As TMZ reports, Giersch is unable to return to the U.S. because his visa has been revoked as of April this year.

According to the website, the judge ruled Rutherford will be allowed a flexible visitation schedule so that she may spend time with her children when travel and work arrangements allow.

According to the ruling, she will be permitted to see their five-year-old son and three-year-old daughter 50 per cent of the time.

However Rutherford, who married Giersch back in 2006 and divorced him in 2010, plans to appeal the ruling.

